mesh                                  macro                                 mesh

NAME
     mmeesshh - 2d grid scan

SYNOPSIS

     mmeesshh mmoottoorr11 ssttaarrtt11 eenndd11 iinntteerrvvaallss11 mmoottoorr22 ssttaarrtt22 eenndd22 iinntteerrvvaallss22 ttiimmee

DESCRIPTION

     The mmeesshh scan traces out a grid using mmoottoorr11 and mmoottoorr22. The first motor
     scans from ssttaarrtt11 to eenndd11 using the specified number of intervals.  The
     second motor similarly scans from ssttaarrtt22 to eenndd22. Each point is counted for
     for ttiimmee seconds (or monitor counts).

     The scan of mmoottoorr11 is done at each point scanned by mmoottoorr22.  That is, the
     first motor scan is nested within the second motor scan.

     A mmeesshh scan creates only one scan entry in the ssppeecc data file with a total
     of ((iinntteerrvvaallss11++11)) ** ((iinntteerrvvaallss22++11)) points.

EXAMPLE

     mmeesshh tthh 00 11 1100 pphhii 00 22 1100 1100

